comments.body:
@baude I mean that good intention to create and start single container pod using single command **Podman run --pod new:** resulted in chaos due to incomplete design. In Docker the command **docker run** means create and start the container. after the command has been finished the container is created and started (container id is printed!) and is ready to serve the user's requests. In Podman it is impossible to interpret the result. When I tried to use "Nginx Pod" The HTTP request failed because Nginx is slow to start and there is no indication of its actual status. I expect that the single container pod is created and started and I can use it.
I also defined the **health check** for my Nginx container but it was ignored completely. Testing using the browser returned random results. It leaves me completely confused. 
Then, I used Podman healthcheck run command to check Nginx readiness, it printed healthy, Browser and Curl tests returned positive result but **Podman pod ls** and **Podman ps** command shows the container in undocumented state UP instead of running or healthy. The pod had CREATED status.
